HEADWORD: Pygargus
<hw>Py*gar"gus</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <ety>[L. <ets>pygargus</ets>, Gr. <?/, literally,
white rump; <?/ the rump + white: cf. F. <ets>pygargue</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A quadruped, probably the addax, an
antelope having a white rump.</def> <rj><au>Deut. xiv. 5.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The female of the
hen harrier.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The sea eagle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pygidium</ent>⟦br⟧
